main event: Two observers in Shelby, Iowa saw two round objects resembling parachutes dropping silently from the sky on October 1, 1955.
interesting points: The observers thought they heard a muffled explosion during the sighting., The objects were described as small, round, and parachute-like., Investigators found no trace of a crash or debris., The initial sighting lasted for about half a minute., Subsequent sightings involved additional similar objects that disappeared rapidly.
witness description: Two 15-year-old female students, both described as credible and having received training as observers.
